getDisputeFee(bytes32).details: Get the fee for a dispute from a specified question. UNTRUSTED.

reportAnswer(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32,uin.details: Report the answer to a specified question from the ERC792 arbitrator to the Realitio contract. TRUSTED.

params._isCommitment: Whether the last answer to the question in the Realitio contract used commit or reveal or not. True if it did, false otherwise.
params._lastAnswerOrCommitmentID: The last answer given, or its commitment ID if it was a commitment, to the question in the Realitio contract.
params._lastAnswerer: The last answerer to the question in the Realitio contract.
params._lastBond: The bond paid for the last answer to the question in the Realitio contract.
params._lastHistoryHash: The history hash given with the last answer to the question in the Realitio contract.

requestArbitration(bytes32,uint256).details: Raise a dispute from a specified question. UNTRUSTED.

params._maxPrevious: If specified, reverts if a bond higher than this was submitted after you sent your transaction.

rule(uint256,uint256).details: Give a ruling for a dispute. Must be called by the arbitrator. The purpose of this function is to ensure that the address calling it has the right to rule on the contract.

params._disputeID: ID of the dispute in the Arbitrator contract.
params._ruling: Ruling given by the arbitrator. Note that 0 is reserved for "Not able/wanting to make a decision".

setMetaEvidence(string).details: Sets the meta evidence. Can only be called once.

params._metaEvidence: The URI of the meta evidence file.
